  <span id="freeText14082573597031168973" style="display:none">First book of 2019 is finished, and unfortunately <b>it was a total snooze fest.</b> This is a "thriller" that starts off with an intense scene where you discover that the nanny has killed the two kids she is watching, and then the rest of the book is showing all the lead up to that... but my god this book is so freaking boring. If it wasn't for that promising first chapter I would have probably DNF'ed this and I almost wish I did because it never went anywhere. I also disliked the writing style, even though this book was so short it felt so dense because there was barely any dialogue and it was all huge chunks of descriptions after descriptions and... <br><br> <img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1442525396ra/16246765.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><b>I'm sad that the first book I picked up this year sucked but here we are.</b> This book kind of reminded me of the thriller <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36553406.Looker" title="Looker by Laura Sims" rel="nofollow noopener">Looker</a> in the way that it feels like the story is going somewhere but it just doesn't and it's a boring story that is really short but feels so much longer because of how boring it is. </span>
